\sin \left(x\right)\:,\:given\:\cos \left(2x\right)=\frac{2}{3}\:\:\:\mathrm{and}\:\:\:\:\pi <x<\frac{3\pi }{2}
\cos 2x=\cos^2x-\sin^2x
\sin^2x+\cos^2x=1
-
x\in 3^{\text{o}}
\cos 2x=1-2\sin^2x \Rightarrow \frac{2}{3}=1-2\sin^2x
\Rightarrow \frac{2}{3}-\frac{3}{3}=-2\sin^2x\Rightarrow \sin x=-\sqrt{\frac{1}{6}}=-\frac{1}{\sqrt{6}}. 
